Description: Runtime Upgrade Test (mixed client fleet)
Network: ./smoke_runtime_upgrade.toml
Creds: config

alice: is up
collator1: is up
collator2: is up

## chain is producing blocks under both client versions
collator1: reports block height is greater than 5 within 200 seconds
collator2: reports block height is greater than 5 within 200 seconds

## perform runtime upgrade (submitted from the second client)
collator2: parachain 2000 perform upgrade with ./runtime.compact.compressed.wasm within 200 seconds

## after CodeUpdated, require at least 20 more blocks AND every aura
## authority to have authored one of them (catches single-node authoring
## and same-slot collisions between mixed client versions).
collator1: js-script ./scripts/post_upgrade.js with "20" return is equal to 1 within 450 seconds
collator2: js-script ./scripts/post_upgrade.js with "20" return is equal to 1 within 450 seconds
